Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.38,0:00:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know there's an awesome\Ntreasure at the end of this sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.61,0:00:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whoever gets it can be King\Nof the Pirates! Isn't that exciting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.18,0:00:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unheard-of adventures are waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.39,0:00:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage! Let that shred of courage grow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.26,0:00:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The horizons everyone\Ndreamed of were separate at first
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:01:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now they can be seen\Nthrough a single telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.82,0:01:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bitter compass of destiny\Nis leading your heart astray
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.16,0:01:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so turn the wheel in the other direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.06,0:01:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.13,0:01:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss aside your bonds and your past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.37,0:01:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can surely smile despite that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.38,0:01:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tears shed trying to achieve\Nyour dreams aren't for naught
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.86,0:01:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precious in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.26,0:01:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.78,0:02:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess was that there'd be five survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.45,0:02:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, who will die?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.13,0:02:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You die!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.80,0:02:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How insolent!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Showdown in the Ancient Ruins!\NSky God Eneru's Goal!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.52,0:02:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.19,0:02:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.29,0:02:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You remember that pretty lady who\Noften played the harp at the beach, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know her very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.86,0:02:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pagaya-san and his daughter,\NConis-san, live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.20,0:02:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are very nice people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They treated me to lunch once.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.14,0:03:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that woman was actually a\Nbad person. And her father, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.18,0:03:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.51,0:03:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.01,0:03:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm not mistaken, they helped\Nbad people from the Blue Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.19,0:03:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.52,0:03:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true! They're really bad\Npeople who went against God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father said so, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Your father did? I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come to think of it, your father is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.20,0:03:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, my father is a member of the\NDivine Squad, so he's been serving God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother always tells me\Nthat he'll come home soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I've never even seen his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.21,0:03:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but he works for God.\NYou have a wonderful father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.25,0:03:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you do! I hope you'll\Nbe able to see your father soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.26,0:03:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Skypiea will be dropped into the Blue Sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.53,0:04:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This nation will disappear!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let that man's feelings be wasted!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must... I must tell them at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.73,0:04:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.27,0:04:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dangerous... That guy's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.65,0:04:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just what you'd expect\Nfrom the game's survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.32,0:04:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, it seems you don't\Nrealize who you're talking to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that you still don't\Nunderstand the existence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.27,0:05:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An old fool who wishes\Nhappiness for Skypiea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.61,0:05:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A warrior who single-mindedly\Ndesires his "homeland"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.28,0:05:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And thieves from the Blue Sea,\Nwho are after the gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.65,0:05:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many hardships in this world,\Nso I don't care what my lambs wish for...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but this nation has a fundamental problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.32,0:05:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have time to spout such nonsense,\Ntell me where the Divine Squad is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.67,0:05:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is your goal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.33,0:05:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The return of His Majesty, Gan Fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.94,0:05:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The return of His Majesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.51,0:05:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. After his visit,\NGod returns to his rightful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.05,0:05:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return?! Are you saying\Nthat you're leaving Skypiea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.38,0:06:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I've got a place to return to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a place regarded as God's home
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the people on the\Nsky island where I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.66,0:06:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.33,0:06:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People call that place "Endless Vearth."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.67,0:06:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, the ground extends\Nas far as the eye can see!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is precisely the dream world that I seek!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.34,0:06:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Endless Vearth is a land befitting me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.38,0:06:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting over Upper Yard...\Nsuch small Vearth... is a petty triviality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.06,0:06:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. The root of your\Nconflicts lies in a deeper place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.53,0:06:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.40,0:06:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was born in the sky, though it's not a cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.74,0:06:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It lives in the sky, though it's not a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.41,0:07:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A nation rooted in the sky... This nation\Nitself is an utterly unnatural existence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.05,0:07:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soil has a place to return to.\NSo do people and God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing you should be surprised about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As God, I'm only adhering to...\Nyes, the province of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.41,0:07:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I will drag down\Nevery human from this sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.45,0:07:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to wipe out this nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.12,0:07:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be conceited, Eneru!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The term "God" is just a title used\Nto refer to the leader of this nation!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.80,0:07:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, up until now, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.80,0:08:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real "God" does not\Nlive in the human world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Former God, Gan Fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.45,0:08:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were worried about the\NDivine Squad, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.79,0:08:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six years ago, you lost against my forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.46,0:08:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I took your 650\Nsubordinates under my charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.13,0:08:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just this morning, they finished the\Nwork I asked them to do on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.47,0:08:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.97,0:08:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who are standing on this\Nisland right now are the six of us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.81,0:08:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.81,0:08:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I wanted to harm them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.02,0:08:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I told them my goal...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.52,0:08:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they challenged me with\Nangry looks on their faces!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.86,0:09:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They all have family on Angel Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know. I have to bury\Ntheir families soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.47,0:09:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.51,0:09:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a devil?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.03,0:09:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five million... ten million... twenty million...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.54,0:09:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't we...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.54,0:09:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't we the evil ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shandian warriors...\NThey attack God's Island, Upper Yard,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.92,0:09:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only because they want to get back\Nthe homeland of their ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.59,0:10:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you thinking about that again, my Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look at the blessed\Nlives of people in Skypiea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It all started when our ancestors\Ntook away Upper Yard 400 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.60,0:10:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it our duty to carry on this battle\Nand protect that blessing for this nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.61,0:10:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we've tried to\Nnegotiate as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.98,0:10:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who cannot understand it do not\Ndeserve your compassion any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.32,0:10:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,400 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.66,0:10:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time for us, or for them,\Nto accept defeat may have long passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.68,0:10:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy Attack! Enemy Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.33,0:11:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this an attack by the Shandians?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.00,0:11:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not the Shandians!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.67,0:11:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man who calls himself God Eneru...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.17,0:11:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Eneru?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.34,0:11:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could he be to call himself\NGod in front of His Lordship?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.06,0:11:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Divine Squad, huh?\NThey weren't as strong as I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.57,0:11:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.07,0:11:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you should at least acknowledge\Nthat they were loyal to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.07,0:11:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eneru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:12:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're God? No, former God, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.31,0:12:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.41,0:12:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eneru-sama, what are we going\Nto do with this old former God?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.41,0:12:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just throw him in the sea or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.12,0:12:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably couldn't even\Nbe used for manual labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.12,0:12:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, this is quite a nice shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.12,0:12:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what we need is the Divine Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.46,0:12:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have them work very\Nhard as my subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.80,0:12:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are my subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.13,0:13:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! You are not "God" any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.08,0:13:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,20 million volt...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.45,0:13:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Vaari!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.12,0:13:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird knight!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.46,0:13:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God exists in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.80,0:13:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How mortifying...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.14,0:13:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That God... is me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.48,0:13:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Devil Fruit's Power?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.01,0:13:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably the Rumble-Rumble Fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.85,0:13:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm not mistaken,\Namong the many kinds of powers,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.85,0:13:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's one of those said to be "invincible."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.86,0:13:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power of lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.86,0:14:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightning... There's no way\Nthat humans can defeat him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's exactly the time that I prophesied.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.14,0:14:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...there are five! I'm glad you've survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.85,0:14:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I shall bring you along with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.85,0:14:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the dream world that I'm setting off to!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.52,0:14:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the Endless Vearth!\NI shall bring you along with me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.86,0:14:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.03,0:14:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, I will build an\Nindisputable "Nation of God"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who can live there\Nare the chosen ones here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.21,0:14:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that guy talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.54,0:14:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those subordinates of mine,\Nwho couldn't even handle
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.71,0:14:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a short survival game,\Nwill only lower the nation's stature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.92,0:15:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And... What if we refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.86,0:15:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Robin!\N--Refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.29,0:15:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? It was decided by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.20,0:15:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you stay here, you'll fall into\Na bottomless pit with this nation!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.87,0:15:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably true that with\Nyour power, you can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.21,0:15:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you thoughtlessly destroy this nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.88,0:15:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't the thing you want going to fall as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.88,0:15:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the golden bell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.92,0:15:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.25,0:15:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Golden bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.92,0:15:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The golden bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.59,0:15:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry. I already have some idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.26,0:15:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall the actions you took,\Nthere is only one possible place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.61,0:15:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure that I'm thinking\Nof the same place that you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.65,0:16:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.59,0:16:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think you'd be able\Nto outwit me by saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How foolish...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.60,0:16:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.26,0:16:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate calculating women.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.61,0:16:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.33,0:16:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.34,0:16:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.32,0:17:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got good skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.32,0:17:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you... a nutjob?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.50,0:17:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn Bazooka!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.67,0:17:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kari!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.56,0:17:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Can't be! He erased the\Nbazooka's powerful fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.73,0:17:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still don't get it, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.40,0:18:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The energy that you can\Nhandle is nothing to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.01,0:18:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thunder reverberated...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.34,0:18:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the air expanded\Nat the speed of sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.34,0:18:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that powerful!! The scale of\Nhis energy is so different from ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He's really... lightning itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.39,0:18:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy... We are about to set off\Nto the Endless Vearth together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.06,0:18:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to get so\Nblood-thirsty, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.40,0:18:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who said we're coming with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.97,0:18:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about your\Nso-called "dream world"!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro! Don't, Zoro! He's too strong!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.75,0:18:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I teach your body a lesson,\Nyou probably won't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.12,0:18:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the definition of "God."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.57,0:19:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God has an overwhelming power\Nthat could never be matched,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how hard you struggle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you feel it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The despair!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having all your hopes dashed\Nis the same as death itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.47,0:19:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.80,0:19:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People fear death above all things!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why people prostrate themselves\Nbefore God and beg for mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That just can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Living beings are meant to\Nbow before that which they fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.19,0:19:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pity... That's how instinct is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.52,0:20:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this guy? He's incredibly strong...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.87,0:20:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.88,0:20:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come to be killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.41,0:20:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.55,0:20:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you familiar with a thing called\Nthe "Sea Prism Stone," Eneru?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.55,0:20:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea Prism Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.09,0:20:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm not mistaken, it's a stone that\Ncan take away Devil Fruit powers!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.26,0:20:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... I feel weakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.60,0:20:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea Prism Stone... It's said that it\Ngives off the same energy as the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.10,0:20:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sea in solid form, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.21,0:20:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it can weaken\Nthe power of Devil Fruits!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.95,0:21:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You shouldn't... I know. It's Reject, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.32,0:21:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your body will pay a heavy price as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.25,0:21:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you dissatisfied about?\NYou want Vearth, too, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! I'm happy to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.59,0:21:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...if I can take you with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.93,0:21:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.60,0:21:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reject!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.61,0:21:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.32,0:21:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.06,0:21:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he defeat him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Racing full speed ahead as always
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.88,0:22:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A to Z, we run through it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.78,0:22:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all have worries and fall many times
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.48,0:22:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we just need to rise to the top someday
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.39,0:22:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could be beyond the sea\Nin which the morning sun rises?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.06,0:22:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go little by little toward\Nthe brilliantly shining sun
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.67,0:22:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never treat you "bad"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.41,0:22:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times did we fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.11,0:22:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, we're definitely\Npointing at tomorrow now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.82,0:22:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smile! Come back to you, friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.59,0:22:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to you, friends\NCome back to you, friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.39,0:22:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to you, friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.29,0:22:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to you, friends\NCome back to you, friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.23,0:22:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to you, friends
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.35,0:23:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that people fear God. Fear itself is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.35,0:23:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'm fear itself. Hence, I am God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.06,0:23:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will put an end to this nation\Nin the sky with God's power!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.73,0:23:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I don't have a clue\Nwhat you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.23,0:23:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.73,0:23:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ambition Toward the Endless Vearth--\NThe Ark Maxim!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.07,0:23:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.40,0:23:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
